<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A discriminated union of two or more pointer types, with the discriminator</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// in the low bit of the pointer.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This implementation is extremely efficient in space due to leveraging the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// low bits of the pointer, while exposing a natural and type-safe API.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Common use patterns would be something like this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    PointerUnion&lt;int&#42;, float&#42;&gt; P;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    P = (int&#42;)0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    printf(&quot;%d %d&quot;, P.is&lt;int&#42;&gt;(), P.is&lt;float&#42;&gt;());  // prints &quot;1 0&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    X = P.get&lt;int&#42;&gt;();     // ok.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    Y = P.get&lt;float&#42;&gt;();   // runtime assertion failure.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    Z = P.get&lt;double&#42;&gt;();  // compile time failure.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    P = (float&#42;)0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    Y = P.get&lt;float&#42;&gt;();   // ok.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    X = P.get&lt;int&#42;&gt;();     // runtime assertion failure.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="110"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///    PointerUnion&lt;int&#42;, int&#42;&gt; Q; // compile time failure.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="111"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">template</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typename</span><span class="doxyHighlight">... PTs&gt;</span></CodeLine>
